scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This collection contains the records and publications of the National Association of Elementary School Principals. The material dates from 1927-2015. The collection is organized into three separate series, which include Conferences and Events, Governance, and Publications.

bioghist.head: Biographical / Historical
bioghist.p: The National Association of Elementary School Principals was first organized by a group of 51 elementary school principals at the February 1921 meeting of the National Education Association's Department of Superintendence. In July of that year the group decided to join the NEA as the Department of Elementary School Principals. They established an office at the NEA's headquarters in 1931. In January of 1970 the organization's membership, now over 25,000, voted to become an affiliate of the NEA and to change its name back to the National Association of Elementary School Principals. The group is now headquartered in Alexandria, Virginia. The NAESP publishes Principal magazine and several professional newsletters, in addition to holding workshops and conferences aimed at professional development. The NAESP is dedicated to developing principals' professional skills in order to improve the quality of children's educations.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The materials included in this series have to do with the NAESP's annual conferences or other events significant to the association. The materials date from 1982 to 2013. This series contains convention newspapers, event pamphlets and programs, photographs and negatives, powerpoints on zip drives and CDs, speeches recorded on 3 Â½" floppy discs and VHS tapes, and interviews recorded on VHS tapes. Notable materials include several presidential addresses to the NAESP, an interview with the association's former Executive Director Sam Sava, and photos and videos from the annual National Distinguished Principals awards ceremony.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: The series is arranged alphabetically by title, and chronologically within titles.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series includes materials relevant to the NAESP's membership, bylaws and guidelines, constitution, and organizational development planning. They date between 1943 and 2014. The materials are primarily pamphlets, brochures, and bound reports, in addition to several VHS tapes. Notable materials include the organization's bylaws and platform, tributes to former directors, and documents from the Vision 2021 strategic guide, which contains the association's plans for development, organization, and budgeting.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: The series is arranged alphabetically by title and chronologically within titles.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series is the largest of the NAESP collection and is comprised of news, pedagogic and professional development guidelines, educational materials, public service announcements, articles, and research studies published by the NAESP. Materials date from 1927 to 2015. Formats include serialized newsletters, newspapers, glossy color magazines, bound reports, pamphlets, brochures, bound studies, books, and journals, spiral-bound reports, workbooks, a 5" floppy disc, VHS tapes, powerpoint presentations on CD, BETACAM, and a U-matic tape. Notable materials include a series of bound studies of the elementary school principalship done every ten years, the association's monthly newspaper Communicator, manuscripts of the editorial newsletter Dateline, and Principal magazine.

arrangement.p: The series is arranged alphabetically by title and chronologically within titles.
